@node "Instruction" "FileCheck - Introduction"

FileCheck  is  a  Filechecker  for  the BBS - Program AMMS (Amiga Multiuser
Mailbox  System).   It's  used  to  check Files that were uploaded into the
system.   It  has  also  many  other  features such as recognize filetypes,
stripping  advertisements,  adding advertisements, stripping and converting
of  characters  in File_IDs and stripping and adding lines to File_IDs.  It
will look for duplicate Files on demand.
Nearly  all options can be switched directly in the program-call or/and can
be declared in the configuration file.  Here is a list of all Features:

 · many recognizeable filetypes
   (LHA, LZX, ZIP, RAR, ARJ, DMS, TXT, GIF, JPEG, EXE)
 · Filetype recognition (w/o external libraries)
 · Filenames will be changed if the suffix does not agree to the filetype
 · simple integrity check
 · corrupt and duplicate files will be moved and marked on demand
 · extract the File_ID
 · characters of a File_ID can be converted or stripped
   (useful to convert pc-texts)
 · add a line to the File_ID or strip some lines
 · save the File_ID
 · strip and add advertisements
 · duplicate check with turbomode
 · disable duplicate check for named users
 · disable options for named fileboards
 · use different advertisements for different filetypes
 · direct MAPUS - support
 · direct SetReturn - support
 · textoutputs can be completely changed
 · options will be read from the ENV-Vars if possible
 · FileCheck is the fastest MultiArchive-checker I know
 · all Filetypes are switchable
 · FileCheck is shareware but free of charge!

Since  version 3.00 FileCheck is written in C and thereby it's getting more
flexible and much more faster!

@endnode


