Here you will find all Files that can be changed or that cause changes:


@{b}mbeigene:Cannon/FileChecker@{ub}

@{" FastScan.bat        " link "fastscan.bat" 0} -> script to scan the filebase
@{" FileCheck           " link "filecheck" 0} -> the main program
@{" FileCheck.fast      " link "filecheck.fast" 0} -> filebaselist (used in turbomode
@{" ScanDir             " link "scandir" 0} -> to scan directories for the dupechecker


@{b}mbeigene:Cannon/FileChecker/Config@{ub}

@{" FileCheck.config    " link "filecheck.config" 0} -> the main configuration-file
@{" FileCheck.dirs      " link "filecheck.dirs" 0} -> AmigaDOS-paths for the Duplicate-Check
@{" FileCheck.lstrip    " link "filecheck.lstrip" 0} -> lines to strip out of File_ID
@{" FileCheck.noadd     " link "filecheck.noadd" 0} -> boards where no advertisement will be added
@{" FileCheck.nodup     " link "filecheck.nodup" 0} -> boards where no Duplicate-check will be done
@{" FileCheck.nostrip   " link "filecheck.nostrip" 0} -> boards where no files will be stipped off
@{" FileCheck.noudup    " link "filecheck.noudup" 0} -> Users that will not cause a duplicate check
@{" FileCheck.strip     " link "filecheck.strip" 0} -> Strippatterns for LHA-, LZX- and ZIP-Archives
@{" FileCheck.suffixes  " link "filecheck.suffixes" 0} -> suffixes that can be changed directly


@{b}mbeigene:Cannon/FileChecker/Languages@{ub}

@{" FileCheck.default   " link "filecheck.lang1" 0} -> @{" " system "MultiView Data/Default.iff SCREEN" 0} Standard-design
@{" FileCheck.bigplanet " link "filecheck.lang2" 0} -> @{" " system "MultiView Data/BigPlanet.iff SCREEN" 0} BigPlanet-design
@{" FileCheck.progress  " link "filecheck.lang3" 0} -> @{" " system "MultiView Data/Progress.iff SCREEN" 0} Progress-design


@{b}mbbatch:Upload@{ub}

@{" @                   " link "up-batch" 0} -> an example of the uplaod-batch ..


@{b}The  Returncode of the program is delivered to the shell.  So you can check
it with FailAt or the variable RC:@{ub}

 0 - Condition green - everything fine :-)
 5 - error in argumentparsing
10 - error on generating the file @{" FileCheck.fast " link "filecheck.fast" 0}
15 - found duplicate file
20 - integrity-check failed
25 - File not found
30 - the config-file @{" FileCheck.config " link "filecheck.config" 0} is corrupt
40 - not enough memory (go out and buy some ;-) )
50 - keyfile corrupt

FileCheck  sets  various  kind  of  @{" ENV-Vars " link "env-vars" 0}  that  can  be  used  in the
design-texts and in the line that can be added to File_IDs.
@endnode


