@node "Register" "FileCheck - Registering"

FileCheck  is SHAREWARE and kann be registered for FREE!  The registring is
only  for  me to know who use this program and to decide to further develop
it.

If  you  like  and  use this program register immediately.  I will send you
information if a new version is about to be released.

Send  me an E-Mail and I will send you a keyfile which directly fit to your
AMMS  -  system.  The keyfile will be registered to your Subaddress.  (e.g.
Cannon@BigPlanet).   Therefore  you  have to mention your subaddress in the
E-Mail if it's not the same as in your E-Mail address.

The  unregistered  version  of  FileCheck  is completely useable.  The only
restriction  is a nerve-text at the end of the program which delay the call
for a few seconds.
That can be nerve-racking, eh ?  ;-) so you should better register - NOW!
@endnode


@node "Rights" "FileCheck - Disclaimer"

FileCheck  is  distributed  as  SHAREWARE.   You  can  register  and  get a
personalized  keyfile.  In case of FileCheck this registration is for free!
Any  changes  of  the  executeable  or distributing the personal keyfile is
prohibited.

I am not liable for any damages, including any general, special, incidental
or  consequential damages caused arising out of the use or inability to use
this package.

This  package  includes a lot of other additional programs.  These programs
are needed by FileCheck and I wish to thank the programmers of these Tools.
It would be a great expense for the user to provide the tools himself, so I
decided to distribute them together with FileCheck.
@endnode


@node "History" "FileCheck - History"

@{b}V3.00 - 20.06.1997@{ub}

 - completely rewritten in C
 - faster than earlier versions
 - a lot of new Features


@{b}V3.10 - 30.08.1997@{ub}

 - fixed File_ID problems on DMS-Archives
 - Deleting or saving File_IDs in Textfiles caused errors if there were
   advertisements on top of the text
 - replaced ExeChecker with CheckHunks/Slt
 - various optimizing
 - speed up language/design handling
 - The contents of "FileCheck.types" is now placed in the
   language/design-texts
 - Changed "FileCheck.nodup" to "FileCheck.noudup"
 - added "FileCheck.nodup"
 - new Argument MASKTYPES. Filetypes can be switched off by bit-selection
 - Error-messages from archivers will be suppressed now
 - Changed the temporary directory to "MBTMP:"
 - You can now remark lines in "FileCheck.config" with a semicolon in
   the first column of the line

@endnode


