@node "Fastscan.bat" "FileCheck - FastScan.bat"

This  Batch  is  an  AMMS-Batch which should be startet via an Event.  This
Batch  then  starts  FileCheck and scans all directories which are named in
the file @{" FileCheck.dirs " link "filecheck.dirs" 0}.
The  directory  contents will be written into the file @{" FileCheck.fast " link "filecheck.fast" 0}.


@{b}This is an example for the Batch:@{ub}

@{fg shine}_extern/quiet mbeigene:Cannon/FileChecker/FileCheck TURBOSCAN@{fg text}
@endnode


@node "FileCheck" "FileCheck - FileCheck"

@{fg shine}FileCheck [FILE file] [BOARD board] [PORT port] [NAME name]
          [LANGUAGE language] [MASKTYPES filetypemask] [NOCHECK] [NOADD]
          [NOLADD] [NOSTRIP] [NOLSTRIP] [NOCSTRIP] [NOCVT] [NODIZ] [NODUP]
          [NOTURBO] [NOMOVE] [NOSAVE] [TURBOSCAN]@{fg text}

@{b}These  parameters  have to be delivered by the program-call if there are no
ENV-Vars set:@{ub}

file      - the file to be checked
board     - the destination fileboard
port      - the current port to prevent upload-problems at the same time
name      - the Username of the uploader

@{b}These parameters are not absolute necessary:@{ub}

language  - sets the used design/language
masktypes - allows to switch filetypes off @{" " link "masktypes" 0}
nocheck   - don't test the integrity of the File
noadd     - don't add advertisements
noladd    - don't add lines to File_IDs
nostrip   - don't strip Advertisements
nolstrip  - don't strip lines out of File_IDs
nocstrip  - don't strip chars out of File_IDs
nocvt     - don't convert chars in File_IDs
nodiz     - don't export the File_ID
nodup     - don't check for duplicates
noturbo   - don't use turbomode for the duplicate-check
nomove    - don't move duplicate or defective Files
nosave    - don't save the File_ID back to the File

@{b}At last the only special parameter:@{ub}

turboscan - generate a filelist for the turbomode-duplicatecheck
@endnode


@node "MaskTypes" "FileCheck - MaskTypes"

This   Argument   allows  to  switch  on/off  the  different  filetypes  by
bit-combination  (1=ON / 0=OFF).  The sequence of the bits is the same like
in the language/design-texts.

  1. LHA
  2. LZX
  3. ZIP
  4. ARJ
  5. RAR
  6. DMS
  7. GIF
  8. JPG
  9. TXT
 10. EXE


@{b}Example:@{ub}

LHA and RAR archives shall being disabled. The Bits are as follows:

    @{fg shine}0111011111
    |   |
   LHA RAR@{fg text}

In this case "01110" is enough, because not given digits are always @{b}ON@{ub} !
@endnode


@node "FileCheck.fast" "FileCheck - FileCheck.fast"

This  file  contains the complete filelist for the duplicate-check and will
be automatically generated by the parameter @{" FileCheck TURBOSCAN " link "filecheck" 32}.
The directories to be scanned are listet in the file @{" FileCheck.dirs " link "filecheck.dirs" 0}.
@endnode


@node "MultiDesc" "FileCheck - MultiDesc"

With  this  program you can handle File-IDs of ASCII-, GIF- and JPEG-Files.
You can add, extract and delete File_IDs.
There are three possibilities to start MultiDesc:

@{b}1. Extract File_ID :@{ub}

@{fg shine}MultiDesc e <FILE> [DESCRIPTION]@{fg text}

When  no  Filename  is  given,  MultiDesc's  output is going to stdout with
additional header and footer.

@{b}2. Add File_ID :@{ub}

@{fg shine}MultiDesc a <FILE> <DESCRIPTION>@{fg text}

The  Description-File  given  will be added to the destination file.  There
will be no check whether the destination already contains a File_ID or not.

@{b}3. Delete File_ID :@{ub}

@{fg shine}MultiDesc d <FILE>@{fg text}

The  File_ID  will  be stripped out of the File.  If there is more than one
File_ID in the file only the first will be removed.


@{b}MultiDesc's returncodes :@{ub}

 0 - no error
 5 - no File_ID was found
10 - error in argumentparsing
20 - File not found
30 - other error
@endnode


@node "ScanDir" "FileCheck - ScanDir"

This  small  Tool  scans all directories in a specified path and writes the
list to the file @{" FileCheck.dirs " link "filecheck.dirs" 0}.
If more than one path has to be scanned you can start the program the often
you want. :-)

@{fg shine}ScanDir <PATH> [P|PATTERN muster] [NEW] [QUIET]@{fg text}

path     - Path to be read
pattern  - Pattern of the directories to be read
new      - @{" FileCheck.dirs " link "filecheck.dirs" 0} is written new (default is adding)
quiet    - don't show directorynames during the scan
@endnode


@node "FileCheck.config" "FileCheck - FileCheck.config"

This file contains the required configuration for FileCheck:

 @{b}Line 01:@{ub}
 The  path  or  file,  which FileCheck will append to a LHA or LZX Archive.
 You can use patterns too (e.g.  RAM:BBSADDS/#?).

 @{b}Line 02:@{ub}
 Declares  the  info-comment  of a ZIP-Archiv which will be appended.  This
 comment will be for example showed by list the archive-contents.

 @{b}Line 03:@{ub}
 The path or the file which will be added to ZIP-Archives.  Same conditions
 as in Line 01.

 @{b}Line 04:@{ub}
 The textfile, which is added at the top of an ASCII-File.

 @{b}Line 05:@{ub}
 The Textfile, which is adden at the bottom of an ASCII-File.

 @{b}Line 06:@{ub}
 Declares the Arguments for MAPUS on adding advertisements.

  a - Add front banner
  A - Add tail banner
  t - Add track banner
  d - Add date on track banner

 (e.g. at - adds front- & trackbanner )

 You have to produce the corresponding banners before!
 You  can  get  further  informations  from  the  MAPUS-manual which is not
 included  in  this  package due to lack of space.  You can find the MAPUS-
 manual in the AMINET.

 @{b}Line 07:@{ub}
 Declares the Arguments for MAPUS on stripping advertisements.

  r - Remove front banner(s)
  R - Remove tail banner(s)
  k - Kill track banner(s)

 @{b}Line 08:@{ub}
 This is the AmigaDOS-path where duplicate or defective Files will be moved
 to.
 
 (Hint: If you use a fileboard as destination you should update it with the
        amms-command UPDATE FILEBOARD in your own login-batch.)

 @{b}Line 09:@{ub}
 Declares the characters which shall be stripped out of File_IDs.
 (e.g. 13 65, kills the characters 'CARRIAGE RETURN' and 'A')

 @{b}Line 10:@{ub}
 Declares  the conversion for the IBM-Characterset.  That means the File_ID
 will only be converted if the character CR (Carriage return) was found.

 @{b}Line 11:@{ub}
 The same as in line 10 but for the case that no CR was found.

 @{b}Line 12:@{ub}
 Contains  the line that will be added to a File_ID.  This line can contain
 @{" ENV-Vars " link "env-vars" 0}.

 @{b}Line 13:@{ub}
 Declares the flags for SETRETURN if a File_ID exists and no error occurs.

 @{b}Line 14:@{ub}
 Declares  the  flags  for  SETRETURN if no File_ID was found and no errors
 occur.

 @{b}Line 15:@{ub}
 Declares the flags for SETRETURN if a duplicate file was found.

 @{b}Line 16:@{ub}
 Declares  the  flags  for SETRETURN if a duplicate file was found and it's
 allowed to move it.

 @{b}Line 17:@{ub}
 Declares the flags for SETRETURN if the file is defective.

 @{b}Line 18:@{ub}
 Declares the flags for SETRETURN if the file is defective and it's allowed
 to move it.

 @{b}Line 19:@{ub}
 The directory which will be used for all temporary files.  The default for
 a blank line is 'T:'.
 CAUTION! The needed space could be bigger than the filelength!

An @{" example configuration " link "example-config" 0} is included.
@endnode


@node "FileCheck.dirs" "FileCheck - FileCheck.dirs"

You  need  this  File  to  use the duplicate-checker.  In this file are all
AmigaDOS-directories   listed.    Because   of  time  relative  reasons  no
subdirectories  will  be  scanned.   You have to write ALL directories into
this file.  The result is a very fast duplicate-check.
To  save  time  you  can  use  the  included  Tool  @{" ScanDir " link "scandir" 0} to scan these
AmigaDOS-directories and saving them to the file 'FileCheck.dirs'.
@endnode


@node "FileCheck.lstrip" "FileCheck - FileCheck.lstrip"

This  file  contains  the  lines  which  shall  be  cutted out of File_IDs.
AmigaDOS-patterns are allowed.
@endnode


@node "FileCheck.noadd" "FileCheck - FileCheck.noadd"

In  this  file  you can mention fileboards where NO advertisements shall be
added to the files.  This can be useful for private fileboards.
Remember  to  use  the  AMMS-fileboard  names and paths instead of AmigaDOS
paths!
@endnode


@node "FileCheck.nodup" "FileCheck - FileCheck.nodup"

This file  contains  a  list  of Fileboards (with  full  path), in which no
Duplicate-check shall be done.
@endnode


@node "FileCheck.nostrip" "FileCheck - FileCheck.nostrip"

This  file  contains  a list of fileboards where no advertisements shall be
stripped out of archives.
Remember  to  use  the  AMMS-fileboard  names and paths instead of AmigaDOS
paths!
@endnode


@node "FileCheck.noudup" "FileCheck - FileCheck.noudup"

This   file   contains   a   list  of  Usernames  on  that  will  cause  no
duplicate-check.  Useful for users who know what they do. :-)
@endnode


@node "FileCheck.strip" "FileCheck - FileCheck.strip"

Here you have to mention the names of the files which shall be removed from
archives.
You can use all AmigaDOS-patterns which will be understood by the Archiver.
@endnode


@node "FileCheck.suffixes" "FileCheck - FileCheck.suffixes"

This  file  contains  all known suffixes for FileCheck.  Normally the right
suffix  will be add to a filename if the file has'nt the right filetype for
its  suffix.   But if the wrong suffix is contained in this config-file the
suffix won't be added but overwritten.


@{b}Example:@{ub}

Assuming the file 'FileCheck.suffixes' has the following entries:

lha
lzx
zip
gif
jpg
jpeg

If you start FileCheck with an faked filename following happens:

LZX-Archive: Test.lha  -> Test.lzx
LZX-Archive: Test.jpeg -> Test.lzx
LZX-Archive: TestV1.25 -> TestV1.25.lzx
@endnode


@node "FileCheck.types" "FileCheck - FileCheck.types"

In this file the strings that will used for the filetypes in FileCheck have
to be listed.

@{fg shine}Unknown File-Format!
LhA-Archive
LZX-Archive
ZIP-Archive
ARJ-Archive
RAR-Archive
DMS-Archive
GIF-Picture
JPEG-Picture
ASCII/ANSI-Text
Executable@{fg text}


--[settingsfile for the filetypes]-----------------------------------------

LINE 01: UNKNOWN FILEFORMAT
LINE 02: LHA-ARCHIVE
LINE 03: LZX-ARCHIVE
LINE 04: ZIP-ARCHIVE
LINE 05: ARJ-ARCHIVE
LINE 06: RAR-ARCHIVE
LINE 07: DMS-ARCHIVE
LINE 08: GIF-PICTURE
LINE 09: JPEG-PICTURE
LINE 10: ASCII/ANSI-TEXT
LINE 11: EXECUTABLE

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@endnode


@node "FileCheck.lang1" "FileCheck - Language: Default"

This  is  the  standard  design/language  that  will be used if no other is
mentioned.

In  this  file  you can use all @{" ENV-Vars " link "env-vars" 0} which are kept ready by AMMS and
FileCheck.

One  Area in this file is enclosed with two asterisks (*). You have to know
that the asterisks have to stand alone in the line. If no Text shall be put
out  you  have  to enter a blank line between the two asterisks. This looks
like following:

*

*

If  you have designed a good style send them to me and i will include it in
the next FileCheck distribution if you like.
@endnode


@node "FileCheck.lang2" "FileCheck - Language: BigPlanet"

This  is  the language/design of my BBS (BigPlanet).  Try this if you wanna
know how my BBS looks like. ;-)

For further information look at @{" FileCheck.default " link "filecheck.lang1" 0}.
@endnode


@node "FileCheck.lang3" "FileCheck - Language: Progress"

This is a language/design which has a progress bar.  It was an Idea of mine
to do that.

For further information look at @{" FileCheck.default " link "filecheck.lang1" 0}.
@endnode


@node "Up-batch" "FileCheck - Upload-Batch"

This is an example of the upload-batch:

@{fg shine}SetHFlags m0t1c0x0
FailAt 100
mbeigene:Cannon/FileChecker/FileCheck
Echo "${CLS}" NOLINE@{fg text}

The  Return-Codes  will be given to the Shell so you can handle them as you
like.  See also at Chapter @{" Configuration " link "config" 0}.

@endnode


